    <abstract id="aspace_b260401f26a920347f05779ab8f3f40b">This collection contains sections of the Apollo Operations Handbook, as well as Polytech alum, Bernard Berg's, computation notebook from his time as an electrical engineer at Grumman Aerospace Corporation. The handbook contains information on the spacecraft, subsystems data, controls, displays, and the index.</abstract>
    <physdesc id="aspace_25b4537e8ab4cc0f661c88ec9dda2829" label="Condition Description">Good. Some pages of the Handbook are ripped. There are pages pasted to the Computation Notebook, but all look fine for now.</physdesc>
    <physloc id="aspace_834aa33b4366c3c1cd9b6d22b15334cb">This collection is housed in the Poly Archives, Bern Dibner Library, 5 Metrotech Center, Brooklyn, New York.</physloc>
