  <arrangement id="aspace_5e26dea9a07262f81c21092054e99cd4">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>This collection has been organized into two series: Series 1. Apollo Operations Handbook; Series 2. Computation Notebook. Folders arranged in chapter order.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_571a203e86a6b09f0c2b8d53bc30581d">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Bernard Berg attended Brooklyn Polytechnic from 1950-1954, taking undergraduate courses in electrical engineering and graduate courses in chemistry. Following his studies, Berg worked for the Gruuman Aerospace Corporation in Bethpage, Long Island as an electrical engineer from June 1963 to August 1968. He was tasked with designing the test equipment for the radars of the Apollo Lunar Excursion Module (LEM).</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_a150770d6294c16f610823c43be10f4b">
